@title [markdown]Sharing helps even when we don't know who we're sharing with. Broadcast publishing -- books, blogs, etc. -- have allowed strangers to cooperate, to tremendous benefit. Scientific publishing, for instance, is like that. [Graphs make sharing information even more powerful](smsn-why/why-nonlinear.md#why-nonlinearity-helps): Authors can tailor their content to the audience; readers can design their own path through the information; readers can learn from each others' paths; writers can add to each others' work without breaking the original author's linear flow.
